2923/// Skip over any no-op casts and any temporary-binding
2924/// expressions.
2925static const Expr *skipTemporaryBindingsNoOpCastsAndParens(const Expr *E) {
2926 if (const MaterializeTemporaryExpr *M = dyn_cast<MaterializeTemporaryExpr>(E))
2927 E = M->GetTemporaryExpr();
2928
2929 while (const ImplicitCastExpr *ICE = dyn_cast<ImplicitCastExpr>(E)) {
2930 if (ICE->getCastKind() == CK_NoOp)
2931 E = ICE->getSubExpr();
2932 else
2933 break;
2934 }
2935
2936 while (const CXXBindTemporaryExpr *BE = dyn_cast<CXXBindTemporaryExpr>(E))
2937 E = BE->getSubExpr();
2938
2939 while (const ImplicitCastExpr *ICE = dyn_cast<ImplicitCastExpr>(E)) {
2940 if (ICE->getCastKind() == CK_NoOp)
2941 E = ICE->getSubExpr();
2942 else
2943 break;
2944 }
2945
2946 return E->IgnoreParens();
2947}

2949/// isTemporaryObject - Determines if this expression produces a
2950/// temporary of the given class type.
2951bool Expr::isTemporaryObject(ASTContext &C, const CXXRecordDecl *TempTy) const {
2952 if (!C.hasSameUnqualifiedType(getType(), C.getTypeDeclType(TempTy)))
2953 return false;
2954
2955 const Expr *E = skipTemporaryBindingsNoOpCastsAndParens(this);
2956
2957 // Temporaries are by definition pr-values of class type.
2958 if (!E->Classify(C).isPRValue()) {
2959 // In this context, property reference is a message call and is pr-value.
2960 if (!isa<ObjCPropertyRefExpr>(E))
2961 return false;
2962 }
2963
2964 // Black-list a few cases which yield pr-values of class type that don't
2965 // refer to temporaries of that type:
2966
2967 // - implicit derived-to-base conversions
2968 if (isa<ImplicitCastExpr>(E)) {
2969 switch (cast<ImplicitCastExpr>(E)->getCastKind()) {
2970 case CK_DerivedToBase:
2971 case CK_UncheckedDerivedToBase:
2972 return false;
2973 default:
2974 break;
2975 }
2976 }
2977
2978 // - member expressions (all)
2979 if (isa<MemberExpr>(E))
2980 return false;
2981
2982 if (const BinaryOperator *BO = dyn_cast<BinaryOperator>(E))
2983 if (BO->isPtrMemOp())
2984 return false;
2985
2986 // - opaque values (all)
2987 if (isa<OpaqueValueExpr>(E))
2988 return false;
2989
2990 return true;
2991}

2993bool Expr::isImplicitCXXThis() const {
2994 const Expr *E = this;
2995
2996 // Strip away parentheses and casts we don't care about.
2997 while (true) {
2998 if (const ParenExpr *Paren = dyn_cast<ParenExpr>(E)) {
2999 E = Paren->getSubExpr();
3000 continue;
3001 }
3002
3003 if (const ImplicitCastExpr *ICE = dyn_cast<ImplicitCastExpr>(E)) {
3004 if (ICE->getCastKind() == CK_NoOp ||
3005 ICE->getCastKind() == CK_LValueToRValue ||
3006 ICE->getCastKind() == CK_DerivedToBase ||
3007 ICE->getCastKind() == CK_UncheckedDerivedToBase) {
3008 E = ICE->getSubExpr();
3009 continue;
3010 }
3011 }
3012
3013 if (const UnaryOperator* UnOp = dyn_cast<UnaryOperator>(E)) {
3014 if (UnOp->getOpcode() == UO_Extension) {
3015 E = UnOp->getSubExpr();
3016 continue;
3017 }
3018 }
3019
3020 if (const MaterializeTemporaryExpr *M
3021 = dyn_cast<MaterializeTemporaryExpr>(E)) {
3022 E = M->GetTemporaryExpr();
3023 continue;
3024 }
3025
3026 break;
3027 }
3028
3029 if (const CXXThisExpr *This = dyn_cast<CXXThisExpr>(E))
3030 return This->isImplicit();
3031
3032 return false;
3033}

3044
3045bool Expr::isConstantInitializer(ASTContext &Ctx, bool IsForRef,
3046 const Expr **Culprit) const {
3047 assert(!isValueDependent() &&
3048 "Expression evaluator can't be called on a dependent expression.");
3049
3050 // This function is attempting whether an expression is an initializer
3051 // which can be evaluated at compile-time. It very closely parallels
3052 // ConstExprEmitter in CGExprConstant.cpp; if they don't match, it
3053 // will lead to unexpected results. Like ConstExprEmitter, it falls back
3054 // to isEvaluatable most of the time.
3055 //
3056 // If we ever capture reference-binding directly in the AST, we can
3057 // kill the second parameter.
3058
3059 if (IsForRef) {
3060 EvalResult Result;
3061 if (EvaluateAsLValue(Result, Ctx) && !Result.HasSideEffects)
3062 return true;
3063 if (Culprit)
3064 *Culprit = this;
3065 return false;
3066 }
3067
3068 switch (getStmtClass()) {
3069 default: break;
3070 case StringLiteralClass:
3071 case ObjCEncodeExprClass:
3072 return true;
3073 case CXXTemporaryObjectExprClass:
3074 case CXXConstructExprClass: {
3075 const CXXConstructExpr *CE = cast<CXXConstructExpr>(this);
3076
3077 if (CE->getConstructor()->isTrivial() &&
3078 CE->getConstructor()->getParent()->hasTrivialDestructor()) {
3079 // Trivial default constructor
3080 if (!CE->getNumArgs()) return true;
3081
3082 // Trivial copy constructor
3083 assert(CE->getNumArgs() == 1 && "trivial ctor with > 1 argument");
3084 return CE->getArg(0)->isConstantInitializer(Ctx, false, Culprit);
3085 }
3086
3087 break;
3088 }
3089 case ConstantExprClass: {
3090 // FIXME: We should be able to return "true" here, but it can lead to extra
3091 // error messages. E.g. in Sema/array-init.c.
3092 const Expr *Exp = cast<ConstantExpr>(this)->getSubExpr();
3093 return Exp->isConstantInitializer(Ctx, false, Culprit);
3094 }
3095 case CompoundLiteralExprClass: {
3096 // This handles gcc's extension that allows global initializers like
3097 // "struct x {int x;} x = (struct x) {};".
3098 // FIXME: This accepts other cases it shouldn't!
3099 const Expr *Exp = cast<CompoundLiteralExpr>(this)->getInitializer();
3100 return Exp->isConstantInitializer(Ctx, false, Culprit);
3101 }
3102 case DesignatedInitUpdateExprClass: {
3103 const DesignatedInitUpdateExpr *DIUE = cast<DesignatedInitUpdateExpr>(this);
3104 return DIUE->getBase()->isConstantInitializer(Ctx, false, Culprit) &&
3105 DIUE->getUpdater()->isConstantInitializer(Ctx, false, Culprit);
3106 }
3107 case InitListExprClass: {
3108 const InitListExpr *ILE = cast<InitListExpr>(this);
3109 assert(ILE->isSemanticForm() && "InitListExpr must be in semantic form");
3110 if (ILE->getType()->isArrayType()) {
3111 unsigned numInits = ILE->getNumInits();
3112 for (unsigned i = 0; i < numInits; i++) {
3113 if (!ILE->getInit(i)->isConstantInitializer(Ctx, false, Culprit))
3114 return false;
3115 }
3116 return true;
3117 }
3118
3119 if (ILE->getType()->isRecordType()) {
3120 unsigned ElementNo = 0;
3121 RecordDecl *RD = ILE->getType()->getAs<RecordType>()->getDecl();
3122 for (const auto *Field : RD->fields()) {
3123 // If this is a union, skip all the fields that aren't being initialized.
3124 if (RD->isUnion() && ILE->getInitializedFieldInUnion() != Field)
3125 continue;
3126
3127 // Don't emit anonymous bitfields, they just affect layout.
3128 if (Field->isUnnamedBitfield())
3129 continue;
3130
3131 if (ElementNo < ILE->getNumInits()) {
3132 const Expr *Elt = ILE->getInit(ElementNo++);
3133 if (Field->isBitField()) {
3134 // Bitfields have to evaluate to an integer.
3135 EvalResult Result;
3136 if (!Elt->EvaluateAsInt(Result, Ctx)) {
3137 if (Culprit)
3138 *Culprit = Elt;
3139 return false;
3140 }
3141 } else {
3142 bool RefType = Field->getType()->isReferenceType();
3143 if (!Elt->isConstantInitializer(Ctx, RefType, Culprit))
3144 return false;
3145 }
3146 }
3147 }
3148 return true;
3149 }
3150
3151 break;
3152 }
3153 case ImplicitValueInitExprClass:
3154 case NoInitExprClass:
3155 return true;
3156 case ParenExprClass:
3157 return cast<ParenExpr>(this)->getSubExpr()
3158 ->isConstantInitializer(Ctx, IsForRef, Culprit);
3159 case GenericSelectionExprClass:
3160 return cast<GenericSelectionExpr>(this)->getResultExpr()
3161 ->isConstantInitializer(Ctx, IsForRef, Culprit);
3162 case ChooseExprClass:
3163 if (cast<ChooseExpr>(this)->isConditionDependent()) {
3164 if (Culprit)
3165 *Culprit = this;
3166 return false;
3167 }
3168 return cast<ChooseExpr>(this)->getChosenSubExpr()
3169 ->isConstantInitializer(Ctx, IsForRef, Culprit);
3170 case UnaryOperatorClass: {
3171 const UnaryOperator* Exp = cast<UnaryOperator>(this);
3172 if (Exp->getOpcode() == UO_Extension)
3173 return Exp->getSubExpr()->isConstantInitializer(Ctx, false, Culprit);
3174 break;
3175 }
3176 case CXXFunctionalCastExprClass:
3177 case CXXStaticCastExprClass:
3178 case ImplicitCastExprClass:
3179 case CStyleCastExprClass:
3180 case ObjCBridgedCastExprClass:
3181 case CXXDynamicCastExprClass:
3182 case CXXReinterpretCastExprClass:
3183 case CXXConstCastExprClass: {
3184 const CastExpr *CE = cast<CastExpr>(this);
3185
3186 // Handle misc casts we want to ignore.
3187 if (CE->getCastKind() == CK_NoOp ||
3188 CE->getCastKind() == CK_LValueToRValue ||
3189 CE->getCastKind() == CK_ToUnion ||
3190 CE->getCastKind() == CK_ConstructorConversion ||
3191 CE->getCastKind() == CK_NonAtomicToAtomic ||
3192 CE->getCastKind() == CK_AtomicToNonAtomic ||
3193 CE->getCastKind() == CK_IntToOCLSampler)
3194 return CE->getSubExpr()->isConstantInitializer(Ctx, false, Culprit);
3195
3196 break;
3197 }
3198 case MaterializeTemporaryExprClass:
3199 return cast<MaterializeTemporaryExpr>(this)->GetTemporaryExpr()
3200 ->isConstantInitializer(Ctx, false, Culprit);
3201
3202 case SubstNonTypeTemplateParmExprClass:
3203 return cast<SubstNonTypeTemplateParmExpr>(this)->getReplacement()
3204 ->isConstantInitializer(Ctx, false, Culprit);
3205 case CXXDefaultArgExprClass:
3206 return cast<CXXDefaultArgExpr>(this)->getExpr()
3207 ->isConstantInitializer(Ctx, false, Culprit);
3208 case CXXDefaultInitExprClass:
3209 return cast<CXXDefaultInitExpr>(this)->getExpr()
3210 ->isConstantInitializer(Ctx, false, Culprit);
3211 }
3212 // Allow certain forms of UB in constant initializers: signed integer
3213 // overflow and floating-point division by zero. We'll give a warning on
3214 // these, but they're common enough that we have to accept them.
3215 if (isEvaluatable(Ctx, SE_AllowUndefinedBehavior))
3216 return true;
3217 if (Culprit)
3218 *Culprit = this;
3219 return false;
3220}
3221
3222bool CallExpr::isBuiltinAssumeFalse(const ASTContext &Ctx) const {
3223 const FunctionDecl* FD = getDirectCallee();
3224 if (!FD || (FD->getBuiltinID() != Builtin::BI__assume &&
3225 FD->getBuiltinID() != Builtin::BI__builtin_assume))
3226 return false;
3227
3228 const Expr* Arg = getArg(0);
3229 bool ArgVal;
3230 return !Arg->isValueDependent() &&
3231 Arg->EvaluateAsBooleanCondition(ArgVal, Ctx) && !ArgVal;
3232}

3235 /// Look for any side effects within a Stmt.
3236 class SideEffectFinder : public ConstEvaluatedExprVisitor<SideEffectFinder> {
3237 typedef ConstEvaluatedExprVisitor<SideEffectFinder> Inherited;
3238 const bool IncludePossibleEffects;
3239 bool HasSideEffects;
3240
3241 public:
3242 explicit SideEffectFinder(const ASTContext &Context, bool IncludePossible)
3243 : Inherited(Context),
3244 IncludePossibleEffects(IncludePossible), HasSideEffects(false) { }
3245
3246 bool hasSideEffects() const { return HasSideEffects; }
3247
3248 void VisitExpr(const Expr *E) {
3249 if (!HasSideEffects &&
3250 E->HasSideEffects(Context, IncludePossibleEffects))
3251 HasSideEffects = true;
3252 }
3253 };
3254}
3255
3256bool Expr::HasSideEffects(const ASTContext &Ctx,
3257 bool IncludePossibleEffects) const {
3258 // In circumstances where we care about definite side effects instead of
3259 // potential side effects, we want to ignore expressions that are part of a
3260 // macro expansion as a potential side effect.
3261 if (!IncludePossibleEffects && getExprLoc().isMacroID())
3262 return false;
3263
3264 if (isInstantiationDependent())
3265 return IncludePossibleEffects;
3266
3267 switch (getStmtClass()) {
3268 case NoStmtClass:
3269 #define ABSTRACT_STMT(Type)
3270 #define STMT(Type, Base) case Type##Class:
3271 #define EXPR(Type, Base)
3272 #include "clang/AST/StmtNodes.inc"
3273 llvm_unreachable("unexpected Expr kind");
3274
3275 case DependentScopeDeclRefExprClass:
3276 case CXXUnresolvedConstructExprClass:
3277 case CXXDependentScopeMemberExprClass:
3278 case UnresolvedLookupExprClass:
3279 case UnresolvedMemberExprClass:
3280 case PackExpansionExprClass:
3281 case SubstNonTypeTemplateParmPackExprClass:
3282 case FunctionParmPackExprClass:
3283 case TypoExprClass:
3284 case CXXFoldExprClass:
3285 llvm_unreachable("shouldn't see dependent / unresolved nodes here");
3286
3287 case DeclRefExprClass:
3288 case ObjCIvarRefExprClass:
3289 case PredefinedExprClass:
3290 case IntegerLiteralClass:
3291 case FixedPointLiteralClass:
3292 case FloatingLiteralClass:
3293 case ImaginaryLiteralClass:
3294 case StringLiteralClass:
3295 case CharacterLiteralClass:
3296 case OffsetOfExprClass:
3297 case ImplicitValueInitExprClass:
3298 case UnaryExprOrTypeTraitExprClass:
3299 case AddrLabelExprClass:
3300 case GNUNullExprClass:
3301 case ArrayInitIndexExprClass:
3302 case NoInitExprClass:
3303 case CXXBoolLiteralExprClass:
3304 case CXXNullPtrLiteralExprClass:
3305 case CXXThisExprClass:
3306 case CXXScalarValueInitExprClass:
3307 case TypeTraitExprClass:
3308 case ArrayTypeTraitExprClass:
3309 case ExpressionTraitExprClass:
3310 case CXXNoexceptExprClass:
3311 case SizeOfPackExprClass:
3312 case ObjCStringLiteralClass:
3313 case ObjCEncodeExprClass:
3314 case ObjCBoolLiteralExprClass:
3315 case ObjCAvailabilityCheckExprClass:
3316 case CXXUuidofExprClass:
3317 case OpaqueValueExprClass:
3318 case SourceLocExprClass:
3319 // These never have a side-effect.
3320 return false;
3321
3322 case ConstantExprClass:
3323 // FIXME: Move this into the "return false;" block above.
3324 return cast<ConstantExpr>(this)->getSubExpr()->HasSideEffects(
3325 Ctx, IncludePossibleEffects);
3326
3327 case CallExprClass:
3328 case CXXOperatorCallExprClass:
3329 case CXXMemberCallExprClass:
3330 case CUDAKernelCallExprClass:
3331 case UserDefinedLiteralClass: {
3332 // We don't know a call definitely has side effects, except for calls
3333 // to pure/const functions that definitely don't.
3334 // If the call itself is considered side-effect free, check the operands.
3335 const Decl *FD = cast<CallExpr>(this)->getCalleeDecl();
3336 bool IsPure = FD && (FD->hasAttr<ConstAttr>() || FD->hasAttr<PureAttr>());
3337 if (IsPure || !IncludePossibleEffects)
3338 break;
3339 return true;
3340 }
3341
3342 case BlockExprClass:
3343 case CXXBindTemporaryExprClass:
3344 if (!IncludePossibleEffects)
3345 break;
3346 return true;
3347
3348 case MSPropertyRefExprClass:
3349 case MSPropertySubscriptExprClass:
3350 case CompoundAssignOperatorClass:
3351 case VAArgExprClass:
3352 case AtomicExprClass:
3353 case CXXThrowExprClass:
3354 case CXXNewExprClass:
3355 case CXXDeleteExprClass:
3356 case CoawaitExprClass:
3357 case DependentCoawaitExprClass:
3358 case CoyieldExprClass:
3359 // These always have a side-effect.
3360 return true;
3361
3362 case StmtExprClass: {
3363 // StmtExprs have a side-effect if any substatement does.
3364 SideEffectFinder Finder(Ctx, IncludePossibleEffects);
3365 Finder.Visit(cast<StmtExpr>(this)->getSubStmt());
3366 return Finder.hasSideEffects();
3367 }
3368
3369 case ExprWithCleanupsClass:
3370 if (IncludePossibleEffects)
3371 if (cast<ExprWithCleanups>(this)->cleanupsHaveSideEffects())
3372 return true;
3373 break;
3374
3375 case ParenExprClass:
3376 case ArraySubscriptExprClass:
3377 case OMPArraySectionExprClass:
3378 case MemberExprClass:
3379 case ConditionalOperatorClass:
3380 case BinaryConditionalOperatorClass:
3381 case CompoundLiteralExprClass:
3382 case ExtVectorElementExprClass:
3383 case DesignatedInitExprClass:
3384 case DesignatedInitUpdateExprClass:
3385 case ArrayInitLoopExprClass:
3386 case ParenListExprClass:
3387 case CXXPseudoDestructorExprClass:
3388 case CXXStdInitializerListExprClass:
3389 case SubstNonTypeTemplateParmExprClass:
3390 case MaterializeTemporaryExprClass:
3391 case ShuffleVectorExprClass:
3392 case ConvertVectorExprClass:
3393 case AsTypeExprClass:
3394 // These have a side-effect if any subexpression does.
3395 break;
3396
3397 case UnaryOperatorClass:
3398 if (cast<UnaryOperator>(this)->isIncrementDecrementOp())
3399 return true;
3400 break;
3401
3402 case BinaryOperatorClass:
3403 if (cast<BinaryOperator>(this)->isAssignmentOp())
3404 return true;
3405 break;
3406
3407 case InitListExprClass:
3408 // FIXME: The children for an InitListExpr doesn't include the array filler.
3409 if (const Expr *E = cast<InitListExpr>(this)->getArrayFiller())
3410 if (E->HasSideEffects(Ctx, IncludePossibleEffects))
3411 return true;
3412 break;
3413
3414 case GenericSelectionExprClass:
3415 return cast<GenericSelectionExpr>(this)->getResultExpr()->
3416 HasSideEffects(Ctx, IncludePossibleEffects);
3417
3418 case ChooseExprClass:
3419 return cast<ChooseExpr>(this)->getChosenSubExpr()->HasSideEffects(
3420 Ctx, IncludePossibleEffects);
3421
3422 case CXXDefaultArgExprClass:
3423 return cast<CXXDefaultArgExpr>(this)->getExpr()->HasSideEffects(
3424 Ctx, IncludePossibleEffects);
3425
3426 case CXXDefaultInitExprClass: {
3427 const FieldDecl *FD = cast<CXXDefaultInitExpr>(this)->getField();
3428 if (const Expr *E = FD->getInClassInitializer())
3429 return E->HasSideEffects(Ctx, IncludePossibleEffects);
3430 // If we've not yet parsed the initializer, assume it has side-effects.
3431 return true;
3432 }
3433
3434 case CXXDynamicCastExprClass: {
3435 // A dynamic_cast expression has side-effects if it can throw.
3436 const CXXDynamicCastExpr *DCE = cast<CXXDynamicCastExpr>(this);
3437 if (DCE->getTypeAsWritten()->isReferenceType() &&
3438 DCE->getCastKind() == CK_Dynamic)
3439 return true;
3440 }
3441 LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
3442 case ImplicitCastExprClass:
3443 case CStyleCastExprClass:
3444 case CXXStaticCastExprClass:
3445 case CXXReinterpretCastExprClass:
3446 case CXXConstCastExprClass:
3447 case CXXFunctionalCastExprClass: {
3448 // While volatile reads are side-effecting in both C and C++, we treat them
3449 // as having possible (not definite) side-effects. This allows idiomatic
3450 // code to behave without warning, such as sizeof(*v) for a volatile-
3451 // qualified pointer.
3452 if (!IncludePossibleEffects)
3453 break;
3454
3455 const CastExpr *CE = cast<CastExpr>(this);
3456 if (CE->getCastKind() == CK_LValueToRValue &&
3457 CE->getSubExpr()->getType().isVolatileQualified())
3458 return true;
3459 break;
3460 }
3461
3462 case CXXTypeidExprClass:
3463 // typeid might throw if its subexpression is potentially-evaluated, so has
3464 // side-effects in that case whether or not its subexpression does.
3465 return cast<CXXTypeidExpr>(this)->isPotentiallyEvaluated();
3466
3467 case CXXConstructExprClass:
3468 case CXXTemporaryObjectExprClass: {
3469 const CXXConstructExpr *CE = cast<CXXConstructExpr>(this);
3470 if (!CE->getConstructor()->isTrivial() && IncludePossibleEffects)
3471 return true;
3472 // A trivial constructor does not add any side-effects of its own. Just look
3473 // at its arguments.
3474 break;
3475 }
3476
3477 case CXXInheritedCtorInitExprClass: {
3478 const auto *ICIE = cast<CXXInheritedCtorInitExpr>(this);
3479 if (!ICIE->getConstructor()->isTrivial() && IncludePossibleEffects)
3480 return true;
3481 break;
3482 }
3483
3484 case LambdaExprClass: {
3485 const LambdaExpr *LE = cast<LambdaExpr>(this);
3486 for (Expr *E : LE->capture_inits())
3487 if (E->HasSideEffects(Ctx, IncludePossibleEffects))
3488 return true;
3489 return false;
3490 }
3491
3492 case PseudoObjectExprClass: {
3493 // Only look for side-effects in the semantic form, and look past
3494 // OpaqueValueExpr bindings in that form.
3495 const PseudoObjectExpr *PO = cast<PseudoObjectExpr>(this);
3496 for (PseudoObjectExpr::const_semantics_iterator I = PO->semantics_begin(),
3497 E = PO->semantics_end();
3498 I != E; ++I) {
3499 const Expr *Subexpr = *I;
3500 if (const OpaqueValueExpr *OVE = dyn_cast<OpaqueValueExpr>(Subexpr))
3501 Subexpr = OVE->getSourceExpr();
3502 if (Subexpr->HasSideEffects(Ctx, IncludePossibleEffects))
3503 return true;
3504 }
3505 return false;
3506 }
3507
3508 case ObjCBoxedExprClass:
3509 case ObjCArrayLiteralClass:
3510 case ObjCDictionaryLiteralClass:
3511 case ObjCSelectorExprClass:
3512 case ObjCProtocolExprClass:
3513 case ObjCIsaExprClass:
3514 case ObjCIndirectCopyRestoreExprClass:
3515 case ObjCSubscriptRefExprClass:
3516 case ObjCBridgedCastExprClass:
3517 case ObjCMessageExprClass:
3518 case ObjCPropertyRefExprClass:
3519 // FIXME: Classify these cases better.
3520 if (IncludePossibleEffects)
3521 return true;
3522 break;
3523 }
3524
3525 // Recurse to children.
3526 for (const Stmt *SubStmt : children())
3527 if (SubStmt &&
3528 cast<Expr>(SubStmt)->HasSideEffects(Ctx, IncludePossibleEffects))
3529 return true;
3530
3531 return false;
3532}

3535 /// Look for a call to a non-trivial function within an expression.
3536 class NonTrivialCallFinder : public ConstEvaluatedExprVisitor<NonTrivialCallFinder>
3537 {
3538 typedef ConstEvaluatedExprVisitor<NonTrivialCallFinder> Inherited;
3539
3540 bool NonTrivial;
3541
3542 public:
3543 explicit NonTrivialCallFinder(const ASTContext &Context)
3544 : Inherited(Context), NonTrivial(false) { }
3545
3546 bool hasNonTrivialCall() const { return NonTrivial; }
3547
3548 void VisitCallExpr(const CallExpr *E) {
3549 if (const CXXMethodDecl *Method
3550 = dyn_cast_or_null<const CXXMethodDecl>(E->getCalleeDecl())) {
3551 if (Method->isTrivial()) {
3552 // Recurse to children of the call.
3553 Inherited::VisitStmt(E);
3554 return;
3555 }
3556 }
3557
3558 NonTrivial = true;
3559 }
3560
3561 void VisitCXXConstructExpr(const CXXConstructExpr *E) {
3562 if (E->getConstructor()->isTrivial()) {
3563 // Recurse to children of the call.
3564 Inherited::VisitStmt(E);
3565 return;
3566 }
3567
3568 NonTrivial = true;
3569 }
3570
3571 void VisitCXXBindTemporaryExpr(const CXXBindTemporaryExpr *E) {
3572 if (E->getTemporary()->getDestructor()->isTrivial()) {
3573 Inherited::VisitStmt(E);
3574 return;
3575 }
3576
3577 NonTrivial = true;
3578 }
3579 };
3580}
3581
3582bool Expr::hasNonTrivialCall(const ASTContext &Ctx) const {
3583 NonTrivialCallFinder Finder(Ctx);
3584 Finder.Visit(this);
3585 return Finder.hasNonTrivialCall();

3588/// isNullPointerConstant - C99 6.3.2.3p3 - Return whether this is a null
3589/// pointer constant or not, as well as the specific kind of constant detected.
3590/// Null pointer constants can be integer constant expressions with the
3591/// value zero, casts of zero to void*, nullptr (C++0X), or __null
3592/// (a GNU extension).
3593Expr::NullPointerConstantKind
3594Expr::isNullPointerConstant(ASTContext &Ctx,
3595 NullPointerConstantValueDependence NPC) const {
3596 if (isValueDependent() &&
3597 (!Ctx.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus11 || Ctx.getLangOpts().MSVCCompat)) {
3598 switch (NPC) {
3599 case NPC_NeverValueDependent:
3600 llvm_unreachable("Unexpected value dependent expression!");
3601 case NPC_ValueDependentIsNull:
3602 if (isTypeDependent() || getType()->isIntegralType(Ctx))
3603 return NPCK_ZeroExpression;
3604 else
3605 return NPCK_NotNull;
3606
3607 case NPC_ValueDependentIsNotNull:
3608 return NPCK_NotNull;
3609 }
3610 }
3611
3612 // Strip off a cast to void*, if it exists. Except in C++.
3613 if (const ExplicitCastExpr *CE = dyn_cast<ExplicitCastExpr>(this)) {
3614 if (!Ctx.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus) {
3615 // Check that it is a cast to void*.
3616 if (const PointerType *PT = CE->getType()->getAs<PointerType>()) {
3617 QualType Pointee = PT->getPointeeType();
3618 Qualifiers Qs = Pointee.getQualifiers();
3619 // Only (void*)0 or equivalent are treated as nullptr. If pointee type
3620 // has non-default address space it is not treated as nullptr.
3621 // (__generic void*)0 in OpenCL 2.0 should not be treated as nullptr
3622 // since it cannot be assigned to a pointer to constant address space.
3623 if ((Ctx.getLangOpts().OpenCLVersion >= 200 &&
3624 Pointee.getAddressSpace() == LangAS::opencl_generic) ||
3625 (Ctx.getLangOpts().OpenCL &&
3626 Ctx.getLangOpts().OpenCLVersion < 200 &&
3627 Pointee.getAddressSpace() == LangAS::opencl_private))
3628 Qs.removeAddressSpace();
3629
3630 if (Pointee->isVoidType() && Qs.empty() && // to void*
3631 CE->getSubExpr()->getType()->isIntegerType()) // from int
3632 return CE->getSubExpr()->isNullPointerConstant(Ctx, NPC);
3633 }
3634 }
3635 } else if (const ImplicitCastExpr *ICE = dyn_cast<ImplicitCastExpr>(this)) {
3636 // Ignore the ImplicitCastExpr type entirely.
3637 return ICE->getSubExpr()->isNullPointerConstant(Ctx, NPC);
3638 } else if (const ParenExpr *PE = dyn_cast<ParenExpr>(this)) {
3639 // Accept ((void*)0) as a null pointer constant, as many other
3640 // implementations do.
3641 return PE->getSubExpr()->isNullPointerConstant(Ctx, NPC);
3642 } else if (const GenericSelectionExpr *GE =
3643 dyn_cast<GenericSelectionExpr>(this)) {
3644 if (GE->isResultDependent())
3645 return NPCK_NotNull;
3646 return GE->getResultExpr()->isNullPointerConstant(Ctx, NPC);
3647 } else if (const ChooseExpr *CE = dyn_cast<ChooseExpr>(this)) {
3648 if (CE->isConditionDependent())
3649 return NPCK_NotNull;
3650 return CE->getChosenSubExpr()->isNullPointerConstant(Ctx, NPC);
3651 } else if (const CXXDefaultArgExpr *DefaultArg
3652 = dyn_cast<CXXDefaultArgExpr>(this)) {
3653 // See through default argument expressions.
3654 return DefaultArg->getExpr()->isNullPointerConstant(Ctx, NPC);
3655 } else if (const CXXDefaultInitExpr *DefaultInit
3656 = dyn_cast<CXXDefaultInitExpr>(this)) {
3657 // See through default initializer expressions.
3658 return DefaultInit->getExpr()->isNullPointerConstant(Ctx, NPC);
3659 } else if (isa<GNUNullExpr>(this)) {
3660 // The GNU __null extension is always a null pointer constant.
3661 return NPCK_GNUNull;
3662 } else if (const MaterializeTemporaryExpr *M
3663 = dyn_cast<MaterializeTemporaryExpr>(this)) {
3664 return M->GetTemporaryExpr()->isNullPointerConstant(Ctx, NPC);
3665 } else if (const OpaqueValueExpr *OVE = dyn_cast<OpaqueValueExpr>(this)) {
3666 if (const Expr *Source = OVE->getSourceExpr())
3667 return Source->isNullPointerConstant(Ctx, NPC);
3668 }
3669
3670 // C++11 nullptr_t is always a null pointer constant.
3671 if (getType()->isNullPtrType())
3672 return NPCK_CXX11_nullptr;
3673
3674 if (const RecordType *UT = getType()->getAsUnionType())
3675 if (!Ctx.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus11 &&
3676 UT && UT->getDecl()->hasAttr<TransparentUnionAttr>())
3677 if (const CompoundLiteralExpr *CLE = dyn_cast<CompoundLiteralExpr>(this)){
3678 const Expr *InitExpr = CLE->getInitializer();
3679 if (const InitListExpr *ILE = dyn_cast<InitListExpr>(InitExpr))
3680 return ILE->getInit(0)->isNullPointerConstant(Ctx, NPC);
3681 }
3682 // This expression must be an integer type.
3683 if (!getType()->isIntegerType() ||
3684 (Ctx.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus && getType()->isEnumeralType()))
3685 return NPCK_NotNull;
3686
3687 if (Ctx.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus11) {
3688 // C++11 [conv.ptr]p1: A null pointer constant is an integer literal with
3689 // value zero or a prvalue of type std::nullptr_t.
3690 // Microsoft mode permits C++98 rules reflecting MSVC behavior.
3691 const IntegerLiteral *Lit = dyn_cast<IntegerLiteral>(this);
3692 if (Lit && !Lit->getValue())
3693 return NPCK_ZeroLiteral;
3694 else if (!Ctx.getLangOpts().MSVCCompat || !isCXX98IntegralConstantExpr(Ctx))
3695 return NPCK_NotNull;
3696 } else {
3697 // If we have an integer constant expression, we need to *evaluate* it and
3698 // test for the value 0.
3699 if (!isIntegerConstantExpr(Ctx))
3700 return NPCK_NotNull;
3701 }
3702
3703 if (EvaluateKnownConstInt(Ctx) != 0)
3704 return NPCK_NotNull;
3705
3706 if (isa<IntegerLiteral>(this))
3707 return NPCK_ZeroLiteral;
3708 return NPCK_ZeroExpression;
3709}

3711/// If this expression is an l-value for an Objective C
3712/// property, find the underlying property reference expression.
3713const ObjCPropertyRefExpr *Expr::getObjCProperty() const {
3714 const Expr *E = this;
3715 while (true) {
3716 assert((E->getValueKind() == VK_LValue &&
3717 E->getObjectKind() == OK_ObjCProperty) &&
3718 "expression is not a property reference");
3719 E = E->IgnoreParenCasts();
3720 if (const BinaryOperator *BO = dyn_cast<BinaryOperator>(E)) {
3721 if (BO->getOpcode() == BO_Comma) {
3722 E = BO->getRHS();
3723 continue;
3724 }
3725 }
3726
3727 break;
3728 }
3729
3730 return cast<ObjCPropertyRefExpr>(E);
3731}

3733bool Expr::isObjCSelfExpr() const {
3734 const Expr *E = IgnoreParenImpCasts();
3735
3736 const DeclRefExpr *DRE = dyn_cast<DeclRefExpr>(E);
3737 if (!DRE)
3738 return false;
3739
3740 const ImplicitParamDecl *Param = dyn_cast<ImplicitParamDecl>(DRE->getDecl());
3741 if (!Param)
3742 return false;
3743
3744 const ObjCMethodDecl *M = dyn_cast<ObjCMethodDecl>(Param->getDeclContext());
3745 if (!M)
3746 return false;
3747
3748 return M->getSelfDecl() == Param;
3749}
3750
3751FieldDecl *Expr::getSourceBitField() {
3752 Expr *E = this->IgnoreParens();
3753
3754 while (ImplicitCastExpr *ICE = dyn_cast<ImplicitCastExpr>(E)) {
3755 if (ICE->getCastKind() == CK_LValueToRValue ||
3756 (ICE->getValueKind() != VK_RValue && ICE->getCastKind() == CK_NoOp))
3757 E = ICE->getSubExpr()->IgnoreParens();
3758 else
3759 break;
3760 }
3761
3762 if (MemberExpr *MemRef = dyn_cast<MemberExpr>(E))
3763 if (FieldDecl *Field = dyn_cast<FieldDecl>(MemRef->getMemberDecl()))
3764 if (Field->isBitField())
3765 return Field;
3766
3767 if (ObjCIvarRefExpr *IvarRef = dyn_cast<ObjCIvarRefExpr>(E)) {
3768 FieldDecl *Ivar = IvarRef->getDecl();
3769 if (Ivar->isBitField())
3770 return Ivar;
3771 }
3772
3773 if (DeclRefExpr *DeclRef = dyn_cast<DeclRefExpr>(E)) {
3774 if (FieldDecl *Field = dyn_cast<FieldDecl>(DeclRef->getDecl()))
3775 if (Field->isBitField())
3776 return Field;
3777
3778 if (BindingDecl *BD = dyn_cast<BindingDecl>(DeclRef->getDecl()))
3779 if (Expr *E = BD->getBinding())
3780 return E->getSourceBitField();
3781 }
3782
3783 if (BinaryOperator *BinOp = dyn_cast<BinaryOperator>(E)) {
3784 if (BinOp->isAssignmentOp() && BinOp->getLHS())
3785 return BinOp->getLHS()->getSourceBitField();
3786
3787 if (BinOp->getOpcode() == BO_Comma && BinOp->getRHS())
3788 return BinOp->getRHS()->getSourceBitField();
3789 }
3790
3791 if (UnaryOperator *UnOp = dyn_cast<UnaryOperator>(E))
3792 if (UnOp->isPrefix() && UnOp->isIncrementDecrementOp())
3793 return UnOp->getSubExpr()->getSourceBitField();
3794
3795 return nullptr;
3796}
3797
3798bool Expr::refersToVectorElement() const {
3799 // FIXME: Why do we not just look at the ObjectKind here?
3800 const Expr *E = this->IgnoreParens();
3801
3802 while (const ImplicitCastExpr *ICE = dyn_cast<ImplicitCastExpr>(E)) {
3803 if (ICE->getValueKind() != VK_RValue &&
3804 ICE->getCastKind() == CK_NoOp)
3805 E = ICE->getSubExpr()->IgnoreParens();
3806 else
3807 break;
3808 }
3809
3810 if (const ArraySubscriptExpr *ASE = dyn_cast<ArraySubscriptExpr>(E))
3811 return ASE->getBase()->getType()->isVectorType();
3812
3813 if (isa<ExtVectorElementExpr>(E))
3814 return true;
3815
3816 if (auto *DRE = dyn_cast<DeclRefExpr>(E))
3817 if (auto *BD = dyn_cast<BindingDecl>(DRE->getDecl()))
3818 if (auto *E = BD->getBinding())
3819 return E->refersToVectorElement();
3820
3821 return false;
3822}
3823
3824bool Expr::refersToGlobalRegisterVar() const {
3825 const Expr *E = this->IgnoreParenImpCasts();
3826
3827 if (const DeclRefExpr *DRE = dyn_cast<DeclRefExpr>(E))
3828 if (const auto *VD = dyn_cast<VarDecl>(DRE->getDecl()))
3829 if (VD->getStorageClass() == SC_Register &&
3830 VD->hasAttr<AsmLabelAttr>() && !VD->isLocalVarDecl())
3831 return true;
3832
3833 return false;
3834}

3848/// containsDuplicateElements - Return true if any element access is repeated.
3849bool ExtVectorElementExpr::containsDuplicateElements() const {
3850 // FIXME: Refactor this code to an accessor on the AST node which returns the
3851 // "type" of component access, and share with code below and in Sema.
3852 StringRef Comp = Accessor->getName();
3853
3854 // Halving swizzles do not contain duplicate elements.
3855 if (Comp == "hi" || Comp == "lo" || Comp == "even" || Comp == "odd")
3856 return false;
3857
3858 // Advance past s-char prefix on hex swizzles.
3859 if (Comp[0] == 's' || Comp[0] == 'S')
3860 Comp = Comp.substr(1);
3861
3862 for (unsigned i = 0, e = Comp.size(); i != e; ++i)
3863 if (Comp.substr(i + 1).find(Comp[i]) != StringRef::npos)
3864 return true;
3865
3866 return false;
3867}
3868
3869/// getEncodedElementAccess - We encode the fields as a llvm ConstantArray.
3870void ExtVectorElementExpr::getEncodedElementAccess(
3871 SmallVectorImpl<uint32_t> &Elts) const {
3872 StringRef Comp = Accessor->getName();
3873 bool isNumericAccessor = false;
3874 if (Comp[0] == 's' || Comp[0] == 'S') {
3875 Comp = Comp.substr(1);
3876 isNumericAccessor = true;
3877 }
3878
3879 bool isHi = Comp == "hi";
3880 bool isLo = Comp == "lo";
3881 bool isEven = Comp == "even";
3882 bool isOdd = Comp == "odd";
3883
3884 for (unsigned i = 0, e = getNumElements(); i != e; ++i) {
3885 uint64_t Index;
3886
3887 if (isHi)
3888 Index = e + i;
3889 else if (isLo)
3890 Index = i;
3891 else if (isEven)
3892 Index = 2 * i;
3893 else if (isOdd)
3894 Index = 2 * i + 1;
3895 else
3896 Index = ExtVectorType::getAccessorIdx(Comp[i], isNumericAccessor);
3897
3898 Elts.push_back(Index);
3899 }
3900}

4036
4037DesignatedInitExpr::DesignatedInitExpr(const ASTContext &C, QualType Ty,
4038 llvm::ArrayRef<Designator> Designators,
4039 SourceLocation EqualOrColonLoc,
4040 bool GNUSyntax,
4041 ArrayRef<Expr*> IndexExprs,
4042 Expr *Init)
4043 : Expr(DesignatedInitExprClass, Ty,
4044 Init->getValueKind(), Init->getObjectKind(),
4045 Init->isTypeDependent(), Init->isValueDependent(),
4046 Init->isInstantiationDependent(),
4047 Init->containsUnexpandedParameterPack()),
4048 EqualOrColonLoc(EqualOrColonLoc), GNUSyntax(GNUSyntax),
4049 NumDesignators(Designators.size()), NumSubExprs(IndexExprs.size() + 1) {
4050 this->Designators = new (C) Designator[NumDesignators];
4051
4052 // Record the initializer itself.
4053 child_iterator Child = child_begin();
4054 *Child++ = Init;
4055
4056 // Copy the designators and their subexpressions, computing
4057 // value-dependence along the way.
4058 unsigned IndexIdx = 0;
4059 for (unsigned I = 0; I != NumDesignators; ++I) {
4060 this->Designators[I] = Designators[I];
4061
4062 if (this->Designators[I].isArrayDesignator()) {
4063 // Compute type- and value-dependence.
4064 Expr *Index = IndexExprs[IndexIdx];
4065 if (Index->isTypeDependent() || Index->isValueDependent())
4066 ExprBits.TypeDependent = ExprBits.ValueDependent = true;
4067 if (Index->isInstantiationDependent())
4068 ExprBits.InstantiationDependent = true;
4069 // Propagate unexpanded parameter packs.
4070 if (Index->containsUnexpandedParameterPack())
4071 ExprBits.ContainsUnexpandedParameterPack = true;
4072
4073 // Copy the index expressions into permanent storage.
4074 *Child++ = IndexExprs[IndexIdx++];
4075 } else if (this->Designators[I].isArrayRangeDesignator()) {
4076 // Compute type- and value-dependence.
4077 Expr *Start = IndexExprs[IndexIdx];
4078 Expr *End = IndexExprs[IndexIdx + 1];
4079 if (Start->isTypeDependent() || Start->isValueDependent() ||
4080 End->isTypeDependent() || End->isValueDependent()) {
4081 ExprBits.TypeDependent = ExprBits.ValueDependent = true;
4082 ExprBits.InstantiationDependent = true;
4083 } else if (Start->isInstantiationDependent() ||
4084 End->isInstantiationDependent()) {
4085 ExprBits.InstantiationDependent = true;
4086 }
4087
4088 // Propagate unexpanded parameter packs.
4089 if (Start->containsUnexpandedParameterPack() ||
4090 End->containsUnexpandedParameterPack())
4091 ExprBits.ContainsUnexpandedParameterPack = true;
4092
4093 // Copy the start/end expressions into permanent storage.
4094 *Child++ = IndexExprs[IndexIdx++];
4095 *Child++ = IndexExprs[IndexIdx++];
4096 }
4097 }
4098
4099 assert(IndexIdx == IndexExprs.size() && "Wrong number of index expressions");
4100}

4175/// Replaces the designator at index @p Idx with the series
4176/// of designators in [First, Last).
4177void DesignatedInitExpr::ExpandDesignator(const ASTContext &C, unsigned Idx,
4178 const Designator *First,
4179 const Designator *Last) {
4180 unsigned NumNewDesignators = Last - First;
4181 if (NumNewDesignators == 0) {
4182 std::copy_backward(Designators + Idx + 1,
4183 Designators + NumDesignators,
4184 Designators + Idx);
4185 --NumNewDesignators;
4186 return;
4187 } else if (NumNewDesignators == 1) {
4188 Designators[Idx] = *First;
4189 return;
4190 }
4191
4192 Designator *NewDesignators
4193 = new (C) Designator[NumDesignators - 1 + NumNewDesignators];
4194 std::copy(Designators, Designators + Idx, NewDesignators);
4195 std::copy(First, Last, NewDesignators + Idx);
4196 std::copy(Designators + Idx + 1, Designators + NumDesignators,
4197 NewDesignators + Idx + NumNewDesignators);
4198 Designators = NewDesignators;
4199 NumDesignators = NumDesignators - 1 + NumNewDesignators;
4200}

4364AtomicExpr::AtomicExpr(SourceLocation BLoc, ArrayRef<Expr*> args,

4375 ExprBits.ValueDependent = true;
4376 if (args[i]->isInstantiationDependent())
4377 ExprBits.InstantiationDependent = true;
4378 if (args[i]->containsUnexpandedParameterPack())
4379 ExprBits.ContainsUnexpandedParameterPack = true;
4380
4381 SubExprs[i] = args[i];
4382 }
4383}

4453QualType OMPArraySectionExpr::getBaseOriginalType(const Expr *Base) {
4454 unsigned ArraySectionCount = 0;
4455 while (auto *OASE = dyn_cast<OMPArraySectionExpr>(Base->IgnoreParens())) {
4456 Base = OASE->getBase();
4457 ++ArraySectionCount;
4458 }
4459 while (auto *ASE =
4460 dyn_cast<ArraySubscriptExpr>(Base->IgnoreParenImpCasts())) {
4461 Base = ASE->getBase();
4462 ++ArraySectionCount;
4463 }
4464 Base = Base->IgnoreParenImpCasts();
4465 auto OriginalTy = Base->getType();
4466 if (auto *DRE = dyn_cast<DeclRefExpr>(Base))
4467 if (auto *PVD = dyn_cast<ParmVarDecl>(DRE->getDecl()))
4468 OriginalTy = PVD->getOriginalType().getNonReferenceType();
4469
4470 for (unsigned Cnt = 0; Cnt < ArraySectionCount; ++Cnt) {
4471 if (OriginalTy->isAnyPointerType())
4472 OriginalTy = OriginalTy->getPointeeType();
4473 else {
4474 assert (OriginalTy->isArrayType());
4475 OriginalTy = OriginalTy->castAsArrayTypeUnsafe()->getElementType();
4476 }
4477 }
4478 return OriginalTy;
4479}

4481bool Expr::hasUnderlyingCapability() const {
4482 // This is heavy and the information should instead be recorded on the AST
4483 // itself. However this would require large changes and might not be easy to
4484 // maintain downstream. We should also try to pass at some point an AST
4485 // context object in order to be able to get the language options, but
4486 // at the moment this gets called from the cast consistency checks where we
4487 // don't have one available.
4488 const Expr *E = this->IgnoreParens();
4489
4490 if (const InitListExpr* ILE = dyn_cast<const InitListExpr>(E)) {
4491 if (ILE->getNumInits() == 1)
4492 E = ILE->getInit(0)->IgnoreParens();
4493 }
4494
4495 if (E->getValueKind() == VK_RValue)
4496 return false;
4497
4498 if (const DeclRefExpr *DRE = dyn_cast<const DeclRefExpr>(E)) {
4499 // XXXAR: or should this be getFoundDecl instead of getDecl?
4500 if (const ValueDecl *V =
4501 dyn_cast_or_null<const ValueDecl>(DRE->getDecl())) {
4502 if (const ReferenceType *RTy = V->getType()->getAs<ReferenceType>()) {
4503 return RTy->isCHERICapability();
4504 }
4505 }
4506 }
4507
4508 // This only applies if the subexpr is an LValue
4509 if (auto SrcMemb = dyn_cast<MemberExpr>(E)) {
4510 NamedDecl *Member = SrcMemb->getMemberDecl();
4511 if (const auto *Value = dyn_cast<ValueDecl>(Member))
4512 if (auto *Ty = Value->getType()->getAs<ReferenceType>())
4513 return Ty->isCHERICapability();
4514
4515 if (isa<VarDecl>(Member) && Member->getDeclContext()->isRecord())
4516 return false;
4517
4518 if (isa<FieldDecl>(Member)) {
4519 if (SrcMemb->isArrow()) {
4520 auto *Base = SrcMemb->getBase()->IgnoreParens();
4521 if (auto *Ty = Base->getType()->getAs<PointerType>())
4522 return Ty->isCHERICapability();
4523 return false;
4524 }
4525 return SrcMemb->getBase()->hasUnderlyingCapability();
4526 }
4527 return false;
4528 }
4529
4530 // Handle unary operator.
4531 if (const UnaryOperator *UO = dyn_cast<const UnaryOperator>(E)) {
4532 if (UO->getOpcode() == UO_Deref) {
4533 auto *SubExpr = UO->getSubExpr()->IgnoreParens();
4534 if (auto *Ty = SubExpr->getType()->getAs<PointerType>())
4535 return Ty->isCHERICapability();
4536 return false;
4537 }
4538 if (UO->getOpcode() == UO_AddrOf || UO->getOpcode() == UO_PreInc ||
4539 UO->getOpcode() == UO_PreDec) {
4540 return UO->getSubExpr()->hasUnderlyingCapability();
4541 }
4542 return false;
4543 }
4544
4545 // Handle array subscript.
4546 if (auto SE = dyn_cast<ArraySubscriptExpr>(E)) {
4547 auto *Base = SE->getBase()->IgnoreParens();
4548 if (auto *Ty = Base->getType()->getAs<PointerType>())
4549 return Ty->isCHERICapability();
4550 return Base->hasUnderlyingCapability();
4551 }
4552
4553 // Handle casts.
4554 if (auto CE = dyn_cast<CastExpr>(E)) {
4555 if (CE->getCastKind() == CK_LValueBitCast)
4556 return CE->getSubExpr()->hasUnderlyingCapability();
4557 return false;
4558 }
4559
4560 // Handle binary operators.
4561 if (const BinaryOperator *BO = dyn_cast<const BinaryOperator>(E)) {
4562 if (BO->isAssignmentOp())
4563 return BO->getLHS()->hasUnderlyingCapability();
4564
4565 if (BO->getOpcode() == BO_Comma)
4566 return BO->getRHS()->hasUnderlyingCapability();
4567
4568 if (BO->getOpcode() == BO_PtrMemD) {
4569 if (BO->getType()->isFunctionType() ||
4570 BO->hasPlaceholderType(BuiltinType::BoundMember))
4571 return false;
4572 return BO->getLHS()->hasUnderlyingCapability();
4573 }
4574
4575 if (BO->getOpcode() == BO_PtrMemI) {
4576 if (BO->getType()->isFunctionType() ||
4577 BO->hasPlaceholderType(BuiltinType::BoundMember))
4578 return false;
4579 auto *LHS = BO->getLHS()->IgnoreParens();
4580 if (auto *Ty = LHS->getType()->getAs<PointerType>())
4581 return Ty->isCHERICapability();
4582 }
4583
4584 return false;
4585 }
4586
4587 // Handle conditional operators.
4588 if (const ConditionalOperator *CO = dyn_cast<const ConditionalOperator>(E)) {
4589 auto *True = CO->getTrueExpr()->IgnoreParens();
4590 auto *False = CO->getFalseExpr()->IgnoreParens();
4591 if (True->getType()->isVoidType() || False->getType()->isVoidType())
4592 return false;
4593 bool CTrue = True->hasUnderlyingCapability();
4594 bool CFalse = False->hasUnderlyingCapability();
4595 if (CTrue == CFalse)
4596 return CTrue;
4597 return false;
4598 }
4599
4600 if (const CallExpr *CE = dyn_cast<const CallExpr>(E)) {
4601 auto *Callee = CE->getCallee();
4602 auto CalleeType = Callee->getType();
4603 if (const auto *FnTypePtr = CalleeType->getAs<PointerType>()) {
4604 CalleeType = FnTypePtr->getPointeeType();
4605 } else if (const auto *BPT = CalleeType->getAs<BlockPointerType>()) {
4606 CalleeType = BPT->getPointeeType();
4607 } else if (CalleeType->isSpecificPlaceholderType(BuiltinType::BoundMember)) {
4608 if (isa<CXXPseudoDestructorExpr>(Callee->IgnoreParens()))
4609 return false;
4610
4611 // This should never be overloaded and so should never return null.
4612 CalleeType = Expr::findBoundMemberType(Callee);
4613 }
4614
4615 const FunctionType *FnType = CalleeType->castAs<FunctionType>();
4616 if (auto *Ret = FnType->getReturnType()->getAs<ReferenceType>()) {
4617 return Ret->isCHERICapability();
4618 }
4619 return false;
4620 }
4621
4622 return false;
4623}

4625QualType Expr::getRealReferenceType(ASTContext &Ctx,
4626 bool LValuesAsReferences) const {
4627 const Expr *E = this->IgnoreParens();
4628
4629 // Make an exception for initializer lists with one element.
4630 if (const InitListExpr *ILE = dyn_cast<const InitListExpr>(E)) {
4631 if (ILE->getNumInits() == 1)
4632 E = ILE->getInit(0)->IgnoreParens();
4633 }
4634
4635 if (!Ctx.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus)
4636 return E->getType();
4637
4638 // DeclRefExpr, CallExpr and ExplicitCastExpr can be of reference type, but
4639 // in the AST E->getType() will always return the non-reference type.
4640 if (const DeclRefExpr* DRE = dyn_cast<const DeclRefExpr>(E)) {
4641 // XXXAR: or should this be getFoundDecl instead of getDecl?
4642 if (const ValueDecl* V = dyn_cast_or_null<const ValueDecl>(DRE->getDecl())) {
4643 QualType TargetType = V->getType();
4644 if (TargetType->isReferenceType()) {
4645 return TargetType;
4646 }
4647 }
4648 } else if (const auto *CE = dyn_cast<const CallExpr>(E)) {
4649 if (!CE->isTypeDependent() && !CE->isValueDependent())
4650 return CE->getCallReturnType(Ctx);
4651 } else if (const auto *ECE = dyn_cast<const ExplicitCastExpr>(E)) {
4652 return ECE->getTypeAsWritten();
4653 }
4654 if (E->getType()->isPlaceholderType()) {
4655 return E->getType();
4656 }
4657
4658 // For LValues infer whether they should be capability references or not:
4659 if (LValuesAsReferences && E->isLValue() && !E->getType()->isPointerType()) {
4660#if 0
4661 && (isa<MemberExpr>(E) || isa<AbstractConditionalOperator>(E) ||
4662 isa<UnaryOperator>(E) || isa<BinaryOperator>(E) || isa<DeclRefExpr>(E) ||
4663 isa<ArraySubscriptExpr>(E) || isa<ArraySubscriptExpr>(E))) {
4664#endif
4665 bool HasCap = Ctx.getTargetInfo().areAllPointersCapabilities() ||
4666 E->hasUnderlyingCapability();
4667 return Ctx.getLValueReferenceType(E->getType(), true,
4668 HasCap ? ASTContext::PIK_Capability
4669 : ASTContext::PIK_Integer);
4670 }
4671 return E->getType();
4672}
